The Speaker of the House of Representatives, Right Honourable Femi Gbajabiamila, on Monday congratulated the national leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, on the addition of another life title to his existence. The Speaker acknowledged the conferment of an hounourary doctorate degree on the APC leader by the Afe Babalola University, Ado-Ekiti, Ekiti State, which he said reflected Tinubu’s commitment to nation building and service top humanity.
Gbajabiamila on his social media page wrote:
“I congratulate the National Leader of our great party, the All Progressives Congress, ASIWAJU BOLA AHMED TINUBU, on his conferment of an Honorary Doctorate Degree – Public Administration (Honoris Causa) by Afe Babalola University, Ado-Ekiti, Ekiti State.
“This is another testament to your commitment to nation-building and the upliftment of humanity.
Congratulations Sir.”

			
